org.joda.primitives.collection.impl

Class ArrayLongCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.AbstractPrimitiveCollectable<java.lang.Long>
      • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.AbstractLongCollection
        • org.joda.primitives.collection.impl.ArrayLongCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Long>, java.util.Collection<java.lang.Long>, LongCollection, PrimitiveCollection<java.lang.Long>, LongIterable, PrimitiveCollectable<java.lang.Long>

    public class ArrayLongCollection
extends AbstractLongCollection
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    Array based implementation of LongCollection for primitive long elements.

    This collection implementation allows multiple copies of the same value to be added. Internally, it uses an array, and behaves much like a list.

    This class implements Collection allowing seamless integration with other APIs.

    Add, Remove and Clear are supported.

    Since:
    1.0

      • addAll

        public boolean addAll(long startInclusive,
                      long endInclusive)
        Adds a range of primitive values to this collection.

        The range is defined to be inclusive of the start and end. If the start is greater than the end then the range is equivalent to an empty collection.
